						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#190;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#147;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#135;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171; (Zombidel), meaning 'Zombies &amp;amp; Zilches', is a trick-taking card game from Japan, set in a movie world of zombies. The theme draws heavily on the film Dawn Of The Dead, with the players trying to escape the shopping mall occupied by zombies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By playing out tricks, you try to remove the weak and useless zombies from your hand, and avoid being killed by stronger zombies. If you can clear your hand of any shopping mall cards, you have got free. Now you need to escape by helicopter or motorbike.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But if you take too long, you might end up back in the shopping mall!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is not too serious, the graphic design is humourous instead of gory.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As of August 2021, we are remaking it with English rules and new illustrations. &amp;#10;We will be using a kickstarter for it. It's primarily intended to help outside of Japan, so be interested!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
